x4freetext: LADON gamma ray beam at an energy 30 - 50
MeV -  compton  backscattering  of  the  laser light
Target cell  is an aluminium cylinder with a diameter
of 3.81 cm full with deuterated liquid  scintillator
30.4 cm of diameter and 15.4 cm of length)

x4code.headerHelp: Error in value of quantity, defined under ERR-ANALYS

x4freetext: The reaction d(g-pol,np) has been studied  using  the
tagged and  polarised  LADON  gammaray  beam  at  an
energy 30 - 50 MeV to investigate the  esistence  of
narrow dibaryonic resonances recently suggested from
laboratories. The   beam  was  obtained  by  Compton
back-scattering of laser light on the  electrons  of
storage ring   ADONE.   Photo-neutron   yields  were
55.5, 90,  125 and 157 dregree in the center of mass
Data from Figs.  7 - 11 have been compiled at
the Russia MSU SINP CDFE by V.V.Varlamov.
